content.text:
- **Discovery of ZLC491 as a Potent, Selective, and Orally Bioavailable CDK12/13 PROTAC Degrader - PubMed**
  - URL: `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39388374/`
  - Direct quote snippets:
    - “Here, we report the discovery of **ZLC491** as a potent, selective, and orally bioavailable **CDK12/13 PROTAC degrader**.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39388374/))
    - “The compound effectively degraded **CDK12** and **CDK13** with **DC_{50} values of 32 and 28 nM**, respectively, in **TNBC MDA-MB-231** cells.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39388374/))
    - “Importantly, **ZLC491** achieved an oral bioavailability of **46.8%** in rats…” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39388374/))

- **Development of an orally bioavailable CDK12/13 degrader and induction of synthetic lethality with AKT pathway inhibition - PubMed**
  - URL: `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39353441/`
  - Direct quote snippets:
    - “Here, we develop a selective **CDK12/13 PROTAC degrader, YJ9069**, which effectively inhibits proliferation in subsets of **prostate cancer** cells…” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39353441/))
    - “Modifications of **YJ9069** yielded an orally bioavailable **CDK12/13 degrader, YJ1206**, which exhibits comparable efficacy…” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39353441/))
    - “Keywords: **AKT**; **CDK12**; **CDK13**; **PROTAC**; **prostate cancer**; …” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39353441/))

- **Noncovalent CDK12/13 dual inhibitors-based PROTACs degrade CDK12-Cyclin K complex and induce synthetic lethality with PARP inhibitor - PubMed**
  - URL: `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/`
  - Direct quote snippets:
    - “...we have synthesized a potent **PROTAC degrader PP-C8** based on the noncovalent dual inhibitors of **CDK12/13**…” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/))
    - “Importantly, **PP-C8** demonstrates profound synergistic antiproliferative effects with **PARP inhibitor** in **triple-negative breast cancer (TNBC)**.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34864331/))

- **Discovery and resistance mechanism of a selective CDK12 degrader - PubMed**
  - URL: `https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33753926/`
  - Direct quote snippets:
    - “...we report the rational design and characterization of a **CDK12-specific degrader, BSJ-4-116**.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33753926/))
    - “Moreover, **BSJ-4-116** exhibited potent antiproliferative effects, alone and in combination with the … inhibitor **olaparib**…” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33753926/))
    - “...other transcriptional CDKs, most notably **CDK13**.” ([pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov](https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33753926/))

- **BSJ-4-116 | Chemical Probes Portal**
  - URL: `https://www.chemicalprobes.org/bsj-4-116`
  - Direct quote snippets:
    - “**BSJ-4-116 : Degrader (PROTAC) of CDK12**” ([chemicalprobes.org](https://www.chemicalprobes.org/bsj-4-116))
    - “**CDK12 (Mutant:WT, C1039F)**” ([chemicalprobes.org](https://www.chemicalprobes.org/bsj-4-116))
    - “**Potency Value: 6 nM**” ([chemicalprobes.org](https://www.chemicalprobes.org/bsj-4-116))

- **BSJ-4-116 | Active Degraders | Tocris Bioscience**
  - URL: `https://www.tocris.com/products/bsj-4-116_7528`
  - Direct quote snippets:
    - “Description: **Selective CDK12 PROTAC® Degrader**” ([tocris.com](https://www.tocris.com/products/bsj-4-116_7528))
    - “The compound inhibits growth of **T-ALL** cells and sensitizes them to PARP inhibitor **Olaparib** (Cat. No. **7579**).” ([tocris.com](https://www.tocris.com/products/bsj-4-116_7528))
    - “**CAS Number 2519823-34-6**” ([tocris.com](https://www.tocris.com/products/bsj-4-116_7528))

    - “**EudraCT Number:2018-003007-19**” ([clinicaltrialsregister.eu](https://www.clinicaltrialsregister.eu/ctr-search/trial/2018-003007-19/ES))
    - “(ie, **BRCA1, BRCA2, ATM, BARD1, BRIP1, CDK12, CHEK1, CHEK2, FANCL, PALB2, PPP2R2A, RAD51B, RAD51C, RAD51D, and RAD54L**)” ([clinicaltrialsregister.eu](https://www.clinicaltrialsregister.eu/ctr-search/trial/2018-003007-19/ES))
